{"id":"software-for-climate-3","editors":["nilesh@terra.do","jignasa@terra.do","cynthia@terra.do","sarahburgess@terra.do","shamolie@terra.do","jasmine@terra.do","jaime@terra.do","jason@terra.do"],"classTitle":"Emissions, global warming potentials and the global carbon cycle","index":[{"heading":"Introduction","slideId":"2"},{"heading":"Resources","slideId":"3"},{"heading":"Conclusion","slideId":"4"}],"content":[{"classId":"software-for-climate-3","slideId":"1","questionType":"media+text","slideTemplateId":"SS1","slideHeading":"Software for Climate","body":["<div>3. Geospatial + AI</div>\n"],"question":" ","notes":" ","multimediaType":"image","multimediaSource":" ","multimediaTitle":" ","multimedia":"http://res.cloudinary.com/terra-do/image/upload/v1691785201/Events/tjwabfsu0xyvccqxbnzv.jpg","slideType":"information","version":8,"editor":"jaime@terra.do","hints":[""],"solution":" "},{"classId":"software-for-climate-3","slideId":"2","questionType":" ","slideTemplateId":"S1","slideHeading":"Learning Objectives","body":["<div>Geospatial and AI are big topics! We&#39;re not going to master either of them in this 1-week module - instead we&#39;ll aim to get a broad overview, and then a deep dive into one specific intersection.</div>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>Become acquainted with:\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>how spatial data is represented</li>\n\t\t<li>top climate-relevant&nbsp;sources of spatial data</li>\n\t\t<li>how to use&nbsp;AI to&nbsp;scale spatial data insights</li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>Map deforestation using spatial data and AI-driven land cover classification</li>\n</ol>\n"],"question":" ","notes":" ","multimediaType":"image","multimediaSource":" ","multimediaTitle":" ","multimedia":"http://res.cloudinary.com/terra-do/image/upload/v1720556881/Events/f9pcoyo0fd8vkxd9m2by.webp","slideType":"information","version":7,"editor":"jaime@terra.do","hints":[""],"solution":" ","hyperLinkText":"DALL-E (Chat GPT 4o)"},{"classId":"software-for-climate-3","slideId":"3","questionType":" ","slideTemplateId":"L1","slideHeading":"Resources","body":["<div>Start with this to get a deep slice of one intersection of Geospatial + AI:</div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://dl.acm.org/doi/pdf/10.1145/3485128\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Tackling Climate Change with Machine Learning</u></a> (2022).&nbsp;Introduction (pg.&nbsp; 2-5), Farms &amp;&nbsp;Forests (pg.&nbsp;30-34)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>And then skim all and/or pick 1-2 to read in depth:</div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.ctvc.co/inside-methane-monitorings-big-moment/\" target=\"_blank\">Inside methane monitoring&rsquo;s big moment</a>&nbsp;- Big picture of methane emissions, monitoring, and abatement strategies. Also a good overview of the different scales of monitoring technology, from handheld devices to satellites.</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.maaproject.org/maap-212-machine-learning-to-detect-mining-deforestation-across-the-amazon/\" target=\"_blank\">Machine learning to detect mining deforestation across the amazon</a>&nbsp;(2024)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://blog.google/outreach-initiatives/sustainability/how-satellites-algorithms-and-ai-can-help-map-and-trace-methane-sources/\" target=\"_blank\">How satellites, algorithms and AI can help map and trace methane sources</a>&nbsp;(2024)</li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://iea.blob.core.windows.net/assets/6b2fd954-2017-408e-bf08-952fdd62118a/Electricity2024-Analysisandforecastto2026.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><u>International Energy Agency (IEA)&nbsp;2024-2026 Electricity&nbsp;forecast</u></a> - page 31-38, re: electricity consumption due to growth of AI\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>a counterpoint:&nbsp;<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://climate.benjames.io/ai-go-brrr/\">AI will use a lot of energy. That&#39;s good for the climate.</a>&nbsp;(2024)</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n"],"question":"text only","notes":" notes ","multimediaType":"image","multimediaSource":" ","multimediaTitle":" ","multimedia":"http://res.cloudinary.com/terra-do/image/u